 mitigate potential losses to the Credit Union in the form of fraudulent or risky loan requestsPerform other job related duties as assigned Education, training, experience:2-5 years of related experience.A two year college degree or completion of a specialized course of study at a business or trade school; or completion of a specialized and extensive in-house training or apprenticeship programPossesses good judgment skills and displays curiosity in attempting to understand the &quot;why&quot; behind skills and concepts usedPossess an analytical mind and makes good loan decisions in an environment which requires analyzing different variables in a short period of timePossesses critical thinking skills and applies learned lending principles according to the unique needs of each member and their risk profile. Displays comfort in using underwriting guidelines.Abel to identify and refer cross-see and up-sell opportunitiesStrong desire to make decision with confidenceStrong commitment to provide excellent member serviceConsistently works well with others in support of departmental and organizational goals, and member needs.Excellent verbal and written communication skills. Demonstrates excellent phone rapport.Excellent computer skills; including, but not limited to Microsoft Office SuitePossess strong organizational skills with great attention to detail.Utilizes a strong work ethic to work independently with minimal supervision while maintaining confidentiality If you believe in helping people reach their financial goals and putting members first, we may have the career opportunity for you. If you feel you meet the minimum qualifications for one of our positions, please send your resume and salary requirements to our Human Resources department at . Piedmont Advantage offers an environment rich with opportunities for growth and development; we hope you will consider a position as part of our team!</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>Company Description:</p><p style="height:6px